# Cravyr API - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values

# Server
PORT=4000

# Supabase
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key

# Google Places API (New) - REQUIRED for restaurant data
# Get from: Google Cloud Console -> APIs & Services -> Credentials
# Must enable "Places API (New)" in the API Library first
# Restrict key to Places API (New) only for security
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=your-google-places-api-key

# CORS (restrict in production)
# CORS_ORIGIN=*

# Environment
# NODE_ENV=development

# --- Push cron (optional) ---
# CRON_SEND_HOUR=23

# =============================================================================
# Render (free web service) — https://render.com/docs/free
# =============================================================================
# In the Render dashboard: New → Blueprint → connect this repo (root render.yaml).
# Keep the service on the Free plan (already set as plan: free in render.yaml).
#
# Set these in Render → Service → Environment (never commit real values):
#   SUPABASE_URL              = same as SUPABASE_URL above
#   SUPABASE_ANON_KEY         = same as SUPABASE_ANON_KEY above
#   SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY = same as SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY above
#   GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY     = same as GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY above
#   CORS_ORIGIN               = * OR restrict to your app origins only
#
# Do NOT set PORT in Render — Render injects PORT automatically.
#
# After deploy, set production mobile env to your API URL, e.g.:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://cravyr-api.onrender.com
#
# =============================================================================
# EAS / Expo (free tier) — https://expo.dev/pricing
# =============================================================================
# Production builds need Supabase URL + anon key at build time. Do not put secrets in eas.json.
# In Expo: Project → Environment variables (or `eas env:create`), set for the production profile:
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL
#   EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# (eas.json production profile only pins EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL; Supabase vars live in Expo only.)

# =============================================================================
# Supabase Auth — redirect URLs (dashboard, not this file)
# =============================================================================
# Add to Authentication → URL configuration → Redirect URLs:
#   https://cravyr-api.onrender.com/auth/callback
# Plus any Expo dev-client URLs you use (e.g. exp://192.168.x.x:8081).
# Site URL can stay your primary web URL or the Render callback while testing.

# =============================================================================
# Google Cloud — billing safety (console)
# =============================================================================
# Create a budget + alert (e.g. $50/day) on the project that owns GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY.
